1
00:00:36,811 --> 00:00:38,145
Hey. Kim.

2
00:00:38,146 --> 00:00:39,771
EPISODE 7

3
00:00:39,772 --> 00:00:42,816
Geez. Is this your first day in business?
Don't worry about it.

4
00:00:42,817 --> 00:00:44,569
- Just buy me a drink--
- Hey, boys!

5
00:00:46,904 --> 00:00:47,947
Wait, hold on.

6
00:00:48,656 --> 00:00:50,615
- What the hell?
- I don't have much time.

7
00:00:50,616 --> 00:00:52,659
So I'll keep it short.

8
00:00:52,660 --> 00:00:56,163
There's an important shipment coming in
from China tomorrow night, right?

9
00:00:56,164 --> 00:00:59,000
We need to make some adjustments
to those goods.

10
00:00:59,125 --> 00:01:02,836
So, we need to borrow your little shop
for just two days.

11
00:01:02,837 --> 00:01:06,673
Think of it as a location sponsorship.

12
00:01:06,674 --> 00:01:07,966
What the hell?

13
00:01:07,967 --> 00:01:11,970
What are these assholes on about?

14
00:01:11,971 --> 00:01:14,223
Hey, what are you doing? Get 'em!

15
00:01:19,145 --> 00:01:20,729
What are you waiting for? Go ahead.

16
00:01:20,730 --> 00:01:22,647
- By myself? What about you?
- You scared?

17
00:01:22,648 --> 00:01:24,317
Scared? Hell no.

18
00:02:18,538 --> 00:02:19,539
I'll kill them.

19
00:02:33,970 --> 00:02:34,971
What the hell?

20
00:02:50,903 --> 00:02:51,904
So what's it going to be?

21
00:02:52,446 --> 00:02:53,447
Can we borrow it?

22
00:02:58,536 --> 00:03:00,704
- Ow, my back.
- Geez, it's so dusty.

23
00:03:00,705 --> 00:03:03,749
You should've helped sooner
instead of trying to look cool.

24
00:03:04,417 --> 00:03:08,211
- There were only like seven guys.
- I had them, but you jumped in.

25
00:03:08,212 --> 00:03:10,046
You would've been dead without me.

26
00:03:10,047 --> 00:03:11,841
You would have been dead
if it weren't for me.

27
00:03:13,843 --> 00:03:16,761
Hey, Seong-won. Location secured.

28
00:03:16,762 --> 00:03:19,181
Now let's get set up. Yeah.

29
00:03:21,350 --> 00:03:24,020
- Hey, you're so dusty.
- Stop it!

30
00:03:26,606 --> 00:03:29,024
We'll be working together from now on.

31
00:03:29,025 --> 00:03:30,525
So I'll speak casually.

32
00:03:30,526 --> 00:03:33,695
- Is that okay?
- Yes, whatever works for you.

33
00:03:33,696 --> 00:03:34,989
I like your attitude.

34
00:03:35,906 --> 00:03:36,907
First things first.

35
00:03:37,700 --> 00:03:39,076
I need you to operate this.

36
00:03:41,537 --> 00:03:42,621
This thing?

37
00:03:42,622 --> 00:03:44,874
Yeah, why? It's small.
Doesn't look too difficult.

38
00:03:47,543 --> 00:03:49,961
So, what will you be doing
while I'm driving this?

39
00:03:49,962 --> 00:03:50,963
Me?

40
00:03:51,922 --> 00:03:53,174
That.

41
00:03:58,721 --> 00:04:00,139
- Start it.
- Okay.

42
00:04:00,765 --> 00:04:02,015
That's it.

43
00:04:02,016 --> 00:04:04,310
Step on the clutch and just push forward.

44
00:04:04,977 --> 00:04:08,271
That's it. Gently. That's it.
It's okay. You're okay.

45
00:04:08,272 --> 00:04:11,024
- Should I go?
- Yes. Step on it a bit.

46
00:04:11,025 --> 00:04:13,361
- This thing is so loud.
- No, look over here.

47
00:04:14,862 --> 00:04:16,529
- Isn't this too fast?
- Easy, right?

48
00:04:16,529 --> 00:04:18,740
- Yeah.
- Okay, turn left here.

49
00:04:18,741 --> 00:04:19,742
Left turn?

50
00:04:38,511 --> 00:04:39,512
That's it.

51
00:04:40,304 --> 00:04:41,555
That's it.

52
00:05:07,540 --> 00:05:08,874
Let me touch it.

53
00:05:14,213 --> 00:05:15,214
I'll take this one.

54
00:05:17,883 --> 00:05:19,468
- Which mask do you want?
- What?

55
00:05:20,010 --> 00:05:21,011
I don't want it.

56
00:05:25,057 --> 00:05:28,560
We have to lure them in.
We're going to lead them over here.

57
00:05:28,561 --> 00:05:29,644
Time it perfectly.

58
00:05:29,645 --> 00:05:31,855
Counting the guys from China,
there are going to be a lot of them.

59
00:05:31,856 --> 00:05:34,024
What's the most important thing? Timing.

60
00:05:36,944 --> 00:05:38,403
We're all set, right?

61
00:05:38,404 --> 00:05:42,198
- Yes. It's perfect.
- It's been so long since my last bust.

62
00:05:42,199 --> 00:05:44,201
My heart is pounding.

63
00:05:45,911 --> 00:05:49,205
Well, it looks like we're ready,
so let's get something to eat.

64
00:05:49,206 --> 00:05:52,168
- What?
- How can you eat before this?

65
00:05:52,293 --> 00:05:55,629
I'm suggesting it for your sake.
You're so weak that you got beaten up.

66
00:05:56,130 --> 00:05:57,506
I'll make you strong.

67
00:05:59,508 --> 00:06:01,427
- You got money?
- You should pay.

68
00:06:02,011 --> 00:06:03,220
You're the oldest.

69
00:06:03,929 --> 00:06:07,266
KOREAN BEEF

70
00:06:17,067 --> 00:06:18,110
That's delicious.

71
00:06:31,207 --> 00:06:32,625
Slow down a little.

72
00:06:33,292 --> 00:06:34,794
Doesn't your boss buy you meat?

73
00:06:34,919 --> 00:06:36,962
I'm so used to eating
expired store lunch boxes.

74
00:06:37,171 --> 00:06:38,506
I never get to have proper beef.

75
00:06:39,006 --> 00:06:40,089
This is amazing.

76
00:06:40,090 --> 00:06:42,676
Real Korean beef is on another level.

77
00:06:43,385 --> 00:06:44,428
He only fed you expired food?

78
00:06:45,262 --> 00:06:48,515
- What a scumbag boss.
- Who are you calling a scumbag boss?

79
00:06:48,516 --> 00:06:50,809
When did I only feed you
expired food, bastard?

80
00:06:50,810 --> 00:06:53,478
Every day.
And only the most unpopular ones.

81
00:06:53,479 --> 00:06:54,854
I fed you other stuff!

82
00:06:54,855 --> 00:06:57,106
I know it's a tough world out there.

83
00:06:57,107 --> 00:07:01,110
But how can you not buy this young man
some Korean beef?

84
00:07:01,111 --> 00:07:04,489
Have the bibimbap with the noodles.
It tastes better that way.

85
00:07:04,490 --> 00:07:06,366
- Really? Can I do that?
- Of course.

86
00:07:06,367 --> 00:07:08,201
I'm going to eat till I burst.

87
00:07:08,202 --> 00:07:11,538
You're gonna make people think
I never buy you anything.

88
00:07:11,539 --> 00:07:13,122
Hey, we were busy with the store.

89
00:07:13,123 --> 00:07:16,126
We didn't have time because
it was just the two of us running it.

90
00:07:16,961 --> 00:07:18,586
And besides...

91
00:07:18,587 --> 00:07:20,631
I haven't had much beef in my life either.

92
00:07:21,924 --> 00:07:24,385
But why did you work so hard
at the convenience store?

93
00:07:26,428 --> 00:07:29,180
Well, he worked hard,
so I just worked hard too.

94
00:07:29,181 --> 00:07:32,308
- Do you need a reason to work hard?
- You even got an award.

95
00:07:32,309 --> 00:07:34,436
For "Friendly Convenience Store"
or something.

96
00:07:35,896 --> 00:07:38,523
Maybe that's a better fit
than being a gangster, huh?

97
00:07:38,524 --> 00:07:39,941
No way.

98
00:07:39,942 --> 00:07:42,569
His calling is being number two
in the Hwasan Sect.

99
00:07:42,570 --> 00:07:45,363
He's just being patient now
to avenge the big boss.

100
00:07:45,364 --> 00:07:47,115
- Isn't that right?
- Something like that.

101
00:07:47,116 --> 00:07:51,161
I can't believe you got an award
for friendliness.

102
00:07:52,705 --> 00:07:55,957
Hey, what's wrong with being friendly?
It's not like it's impossible.

103
00:07:55,958 --> 00:07:59,628
This guy lived undercover for ten years.

104
00:08:00,337 --> 00:08:02,422
What are you talking about? Undercover?

105
00:08:02,423 --> 00:08:05,217
Come on, Mr. Jeong. Be honest with us.

106
00:08:05,968 --> 00:08:07,803
Did you marry your wife
because you loved her?

107
00:08:08,345 --> 00:08:12,599
I mean, we saw you get married,
and we saw you have a child.

108
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:13,766
But we couldn't believe it.

109
00:08:13,767 --> 00:08:15,310
Because in movies, right?

110
00:08:15,311 --> 00:08:18,314
Agents get married and
do all sorts of things for their cover.

111
00:08:19,231 --> 00:08:20,316
Huh?

112
00:08:20,733 --> 00:08:22,568
Did you give him an order to get married?

113
00:08:23,319 --> 00:08:25,945
Why would I go as far as
ordering him to marry?

114
00:08:25,946 --> 00:08:28,781
- You watch too many movies.
- No, that's not it.

115
00:08:28,782 --> 00:08:31,869
There's a limit
to how much a man can be whipped.

116
00:08:32,410 --> 00:08:34,871
It's almost impossible to believe
how low he ranks in his family.

117
00:08:35,539 --> 00:08:37,374
- For real?
- So that's the real you?

118
00:08:37,499 --> 00:08:40,083
Hey, what do you people take me for?

119
00:08:40,085 --> 00:08:42,212
You got married as a cover
to work at the restaurant, right?

120
00:08:43,547 --> 00:08:44,882
Hey, stop eating!

121
00:08:46,717 --> 00:08:48,259
I'm not buying you food
to take all this crap.

122
00:08:48,260 --> 00:08:49,510
- Stop eating!
- Come on!

123
00:08:49,511 --> 00:08:51,387
- What's with you?
- You only get to eat the sauce!

124
00:08:51,388 --> 00:08:53,974
This is just bad table manners!
We get it already!

125
00:08:54,808 --> 00:08:57,727
It's not even that expensive.
I checked the price on my way in.

126
00:08:57,728 --> 00:09:00,188
Hey, it won't be that much.
Order whatever you want.

127
00:09:00,189 --> 00:09:02,482
Plus, you're not even buying.
He's taking care of it.

128
00:09:02,483 --> 00:09:03,608
- Really?
- Order more!

129
00:09:03,609 --> 00:09:05,444
Ma'am, can we get some more meat?

130
00:09:07,029 --> 00:09:09,406
Wow, look at the quality of this.

131
00:09:14,495 --> 00:09:15,788
What are you doing?

132
00:09:23,253 --> 00:09:24,546
I've got a lot on my mind.

133
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:30,094
Like you said, I've lived as
a convenience store owner for ten years.

134
00:09:31,053 --> 00:09:33,722
I'm worried if I can pull this off.

135
00:09:36,100 --> 00:09:37,226
Getting scared again?

136
00:09:38,435 --> 00:09:40,728
Why do you keep saying I'm scared?

137
00:09:40,729 --> 00:09:42,731
You think I'd be scared
of that bastard Yoo In-gu?

138
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:46,193
It's just that they've got a lot of men.

139
00:09:46,652 --> 00:09:49,905
And I got my ass beaten
because I overestimated myself.

140
00:09:51,323 --> 00:09:53,742
So naturally, I've been having doubts.

141
00:09:54,743 --> 00:09:56,245
Maybe my body can't take this.

142
00:09:58,664 --> 00:09:59,832
What about you?

143
00:10:00,666 --> 00:10:02,167
Aren't you worried?

144
00:10:02,710 --> 00:10:03,919
Is your body

145
00:10:04,837 --> 00:10:06,046
like it was ten years ago?

146
00:10:08,424 --> 00:10:12,886
If I was the same as ten years ago,
do you think I'd have worked with you?

147
00:10:15,472 --> 00:10:19,017
There's nothing to be scared of.
My calculations are never off.

148
00:10:19,018 --> 00:10:21,020
You, Ma Gong-bok, Seong-won, and me?

149
00:10:21,687 --> 00:10:25,024
We may be washed up,
but we'd never lose to Yoo In-gu.

150
00:10:25,149 --> 00:10:27,317
So don't you worry.

151
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:30,070
Just stick to the plan.

152
00:10:31,488 --> 00:10:33,365
Then you won't get your ass kicked alone.

153
00:10:34,616 --> 00:10:35,659
Well, well.

154
00:10:36,410 --> 00:10:38,037
Now it feels like a real alliance.

155
00:10:39,121 --> 00:10:40,539
Fine, we've come this far.

156
00:10:41,707 --> 00:10:43,042
I'll trust you this once.

157
00:10:44,752 --> 00:10:45,753
Damn it.

158
00:11:05,439 --> 00:11:06,774
You guys go on ahead.

159
00:11:08,734 --> 00:11:10,027
What? You're not coming?

160
00:11:10,819 --> 00:11:12,695
You said we were doing a final check.

161
00:11:12,696 --> 00:11:14,907
No, there's somewhere I need to be.

162
00:11:15,032 --> 00:11:16,784
Where are you going all of a sudden?

163
00:11:18,744 --> 00:11:19,827
Something came up.

164
00:11:19,828 --> 00:11:23,122
The big bust is just around the corner,
and something came up?

165
00:11:23,123 --> 00:11:24,665
You think I have nothing to do?

166
00:11:24,666 --> 00:11:26,876
I've got a million things
to check before closing.

167
00:11:26,877 --> 00:11:29,755
We have a lot to go over.
Where are you going?

168
00:11:34,718 --> 00:11:35,719
It's all right.

169
00:11:36,095 --> 00:11:37,471
Don't worry about it. Just go.

170
00:11:38,055 --> 00:11:39,807
Go on. I'll take care of things here.

171
00:11:39,932 --> 00:11:41,391
Huh? What's gotten into you?

172
00:11:44,937 --> 00:11:48,314
- But what about the operation?
- I'll handle it. Let's go.

173
00:11:48,315 --> 00:11:50,733
How can we do that without him?

174
00:11:50,734 --> 00:11:52,860
We've gone over it enough. We'll be fine.

175
00:11:52,861 --> 00:11:54,530
Yeah, but he's the one who planned it.

176
00:12:03,872 --> 00:12:06,625
You know where he went, don't you?

177
00:12:07,251 --> 00:12:10,128
He just went to take care of something.

178
00:12:10,129 --> 00:12:12,296
He just remembered he had an errand to run

179
00:12:12,297 --> 00:12:13,757
just hours before the operation?

180
00:12:14,299 --> 00:12:16,093
Be honest. Did something happen?

181
00:12:17,094 --> 00:12:18,845
It's not that.

182
00:12:18,846 --> 00:12:21,265
Gong-bok brought up family earlier.

183
00:12:21,390 --> 00:12:23,558
- I think it got to him.
- Family?

184
00:12:23,559 --> 00:12:25,102
What did I say about family?

185
00:12:25,727 --> 00:12:28,230
Oh, you mean
when I joked about his marriage?

186
00:12:29,273 --> 00:12:31,650
- So his marriage really is a sham?
- Don't ever say that!

187
00:12:32,609 --> 00:12:34,193
That's not it.

188
00:12:34,194 --> 00:12:36,654
It's Ho-myeong's first operation
since he's had a family.

189
00:12:36,655 --> 00:12:38,739
So he probably has a lot on his mind.

190
00:12:38,740 --> 00:12:41,577
He knows better than anyone
just how evil Han Gyeong-wook is.

191
00:12:42,953 --> 00:12:46,039
You mean he knows him?
Jeong Ho-myeong and Han Gyeong-wook?

192
00:12:46,874 --> 00:12:48,792
Did they know each other
before the ferry case?

193
00:12:54,423 --> 00:12:57,550
- I shouldn't have said anything.
- No, you have to tell us.

194
00:12:57,551 --> 00:13:00,721
The guy's pulling a stunt like this
right before the operation.

195
00:13:00,846 --> 00:13:02,764
We have a right to know why, don't we?

196
00:13:05,517 --> 00:13:07,519
When Ho-myeong was with the NIS

197
00:13:08,270 --> 00:13:11,063
he used to work on the same team
as Han Gyeong-wook.

198
00:13:11,064 --> 00:13:14,067
- They were on the same team?
- Yeah.

199
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:19,363
For a long time, until that incident.

200
00:13:19,364 --> 00:13:20,782
They were partners.

201
00:13:21,491 --> 00:13:24,661
12 YEARS AGO

202
00:13:43,680 --> 00:13:44,723
I'm in.

203
00:13:45,974 --> 00:13:47,475
You sure the mole is here?

204
00:13:47,476 --> 00:13:50,186
Positive.
That mole has leaked crucial intel.

205
00:13:50,187 --> 00:13:52,230
It's gotten a lot of our agents killed.

206
00:13:52,231 --> 00:13:55,775
We can't let a traitor like that run away
without paying for what he's done.

207
00:13:55,776 --> 00:13:58,069
You're to shoot to kill on sight.

208
00:13:58,070 --> 00:13:59,446
Roger that.

209
00:14:36,358 --> 00:14:38,026
You know why I'm here, don't you?

210
00:14:56,003 --> 00:14:57,671
- You...
- Ho-myeong.

211
00:14:58,547 --> 00:15:01,216
- Just listen to me.
- It was you?

212
00:15:02,259 --> 00:15:05,387
- The traitor who sold out his own people?
- No. You know me.

213
00:15:05,929 --> 00:15:10,434
You know how hard I worked
for the sake of our nation.

214
00:15:10,767 --> 00:15:12,978
Then why are you not in North Korea?

215
00:15:13,812 --> 00:15:16,565
Deputy Director Han confirmed it himself.

216
00:15:17,399 --> 00:15:20,861
That the traitor would be here today
to sell the intel on our agents.

217
00:15:21,611 --> 00:15:22,946
Ho-myeong.

218
00:15:24,281 --> 00:15:25,741
You're being played by him.

219
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:28,285
He framed me.

220
00:15:29,077 --> 00:15:30,620
He forced me to live on the run.

221
00:15:31,872 --> 00:15:33,874
- It was Deputy Director Han.
- Shut up.

222
00:15:34,833 --> 00:15:35,916
Why would he do that?

223
00:15:35,917 --> 00:15:38,837
Han is up to something.

224
00:15:40,339 --> 00:15:41,965
He thought I'd figure it out.

225
00:15:44,718 --> 00:15:45,969
So he's trying to get rid of me.

226
00:15:47,304 --> 00:15:49,056
What exactly is he up to?

227
00:15:49,598 --> 00:15:51,892
- Can you prove it?
- Well...

228
00:15:57,814 --> 00:15:58,815
Ho-myeong.

229
00:15:59,691 --> 00:16:00,692
Ten minutes.

230
00:16:01,693 --> 00:16:03,570
- What?
- Just give me ten minutes.

231
00:16:06,031 --> 00:16:07,032
My daughter will be here.

232
00:16:07,908 --> 00:16:10,202
I only saw her as a baby six years ago.

233
00:16:11,286 --> 00:16:12,329
Please.

234
00:16:13,330 --> 00:16:14,915
Let me have one dinner with her.

235
00:16:18,502 --> 00:16:20,879
- You're lying.
- I'm not lying.

236
00:16:21,797 --> 00:16:22,964
Just ten minutes.

237
00:16:24,132 --> 00:16:26,133
She'll be here in ten minutes.

238
00:16:26,134 --> 00:16:29,554
We'll just have dinner together,
and I'll go with you.

239
00:16:31,139 --> 00:16:33,308
After that, you can do
whatever you want with me.

240
00:16:34,184 --> 00:16:35,185
Ho-myeong.

241
00:16:35,936 --> 00:16:37,311
I'll come with you

242
00:16:37,312 --> 00:16:38,355
and tell you all about Han's--

243
00:16:45,821 --> 00:16:47,072
Sir.

244
00:17:09,010 --> 00:17:11,887
I believe my orders
were to eliminate him on sight.

245
00:17:13,598 --> 00:17:16,601
I came by just in case. Good thing I did.

246
00:17:18,645 --> 00:17:21,106
Jeong Ho-myeong, you're an agent.

247
00:17:21,731 --> 00:17:23,482
Did you seriously believe his crap?

248
00:17:23,483 --> 00:17:25,694
He used to be part of your team, sir.

249
00:17:26,444 --> 00:17:29,781
Shouldn't we have at least heard him out?

250
00:17:30,949 --> 00:17:32,451
Heard him out?

251
00:17:34,244 --> 00:17:35,412
It's just...

252
00:17:36,079 --> 00:17:39,416
He said he wasn't here to make a deal.
He said his daughter was coming.

253
00:17:40,667 --> 00:17:42,335
He said he'd come with us after they eat.

254
00:17:45,046 --> 00:17:46,673
And you believe that crap?

255
00:17:48,216 --> 00:17:49,718
Where is his daughter then?

256
00:17:54,097 --> 00:17:58,560
You know that such sentiments
are just a weakness for an agent.

257
00:18:03,106 --> 00:18:04,858
I've wasted enough time on this.

258
00:18:07,360 --> 00:18:08,695
Clean up this mess.

259
00:19:08,463 --> 00:19:10,631
That incident must've been
a huge shock to him.

260
00:19:10,632 --> 00:19:13,552
He asked to be taken off field duty
several times.

261
00:19:14,553 --> 00:19:15,887
But it was denied every time.

262
00:19:18,098 --> 00:19:21,351
If Han Gyeong-wook found out
that Ho-myeong is married and has a son...

263
00:19:22,185 --> 00:19:23,520
There's no telling what he'd do.

264
00:19:24,312 --> 00:19:27,649
Ho-myeong never showed it,
but he must have been worried.

265
00:19:39,536 --> 00:19:42,037
You want me to pull out
from the restaurant?

266
00:19:42,038 --> 00:19:43,122
7 YEARS AGO

267
00:19:43,123 --> 00:19:44,748
Yeah.

268
00:19:44,749 --> 00:19:47,711
You've been here all this time
without a single sign of Bulgae.

269
00:19:47,836 --> 00:19:49,629
I know, but still.

270
00:19:51,256 --> 00:19:53,090
Is it really necessary to move?

271
00:19:53,091 --> 00:19:56,010
Staying in one place too long
could compromise your cover.

272
00:19:56,011 --> 00:19:57,345
You know that.

273
00:19:58,972 --> 00:20:01,766
It's time to move.
Start wrapping things up.

274
00:20:04,644 --> 00:20:06,146
Yeah. Okay.

275
00:20:08,732 --> 00:20:10,025
Wrap things up.

276
00:20:13,570 --> 00:20:14,571
There.

277
00:20:14,988 --> 00:20:17,449
- Here's your jjamppong.
- Thank you.

278
00:20:47,228 --> 00:20:49,397
- Hey, Ho-myeong.
- Yeah?

279
00:20:49,981 --> 00:20:53,777
I have to talk to you about something
after we close.

280
00:20:54,444 --> 00:20:56,196
- To me?
- Yeah.

281
00:21:02,452 --> 00:21:04,621
No, I'm not drinking.

282
00:21:05,580 --> 00:21:08,541
- Why not?
- Well, the thing is...

283
00:21:14,673 --> 00:21:15,715
Ho-myeong.

284
00:21:16,633 --> 00:21:18,968
Remember how I said
I haven't been feeling well lately?

285
00:21:19,594 --> 00:21:21,054
You're still not feeling well?

286
00:21:23,139 --> 00:21:24,640
Well...

287
00:21:24,641 --> 00:21:26,142
I'm pregnant.

288
00:21:36,945 --> 00:21:38,363
Pregnant?

289
00:21:39,989 --> 00:21:43,743
I went to the doctor yesterday.
I'm eight weeks in.

290
00:21:48,164 --> 00:21:50,583
I'm not telling you this to pressure you.

291
00:21:50,959 --> 00:21:52,836
I'll handle it.

292
00:21:52,961 --> 00:21:54,462
What do you mean you'll handle it?

293
00:21:56,965 --> 00:21:59,426
Honestly, you and I?

294
00:22:00,301 --> 00:22:04,472
What we have is just a fling, isn't it?

295
00:22:06,850 --> 00:22:08,226
What are you saying?

296
00:22:10,603 --> 00:22:15,525
We've been seeing each other
for a long time.

297
00:22:16,568 --> 00:22:18,069
But I don't know much about you.

298
00:22:19,320 --> 00:22:20,780
Barely anything, really.

299
00:22:21,781 --> 00:22:26,369
Like who you were before,
or why you came to Yeongseon Island.

300
00:22:27,287 --> 00:22:31,458
I've never even heard you mention
your parents, siblings, or friends.

301
00:22:32,959 --> 00:22:34,085
And you don't...

302
00:22:34,836 --> 00:22:36,880
You don't exactly have plans

303
00:22:37,630 --> 00:22:39,132
to tell me

304
00:22:40,175 --> 00:22:42,385
about any of that, do you?

305
00:22:51,978 --> 00:22:55,732
I'm almost 40,
so having a baby is a bit...

306
00:22:56,649 --> 00:22:57,650
scary.

307
00:22:58,610 --> 00:23:01,528
And even if I had a baby,

308
00:23:01,529 --> 00:23:03,363
I'd have no idea how to raise it.

309
00:23:03,364 --> 00:23:05,033
Plus, I'm busy with the store.

310
00:23:06,034 --> 00:23:08,870
I've said what I needed to say,
so just enjoy your drink.

311
00:23:09,871 --> 00:23:11,122
I'm not drinking.

312
00:23:11,915 --> 00:23:12,916
Huh?

313
00:23:16,711 --> 00:23:18,087
I won't drink alone.

314
00:23:19,631 --> 00:23:20,965
Let's drink after the baby is born.

315
00:23:24,928 --> 00:23:25,929
What...

316
00:23:26,763 --> 00:23:29,057
What do you mean by that?

317
00:23:30,975 --> 00:23:32,101
Let's have this baby.

318
00:23:33,311 --> 00:23:36,855
Is it really that simple for you?

319
00:23:36,856 --> 00:23:38,191
It's not.

320
00:23:40,360 --> 00:23:41,653
The truth is...

321
00:23:43,404 --> 00:23:45,156
My parents passed away when I was young.

322
00:23:46,908 --> 00:23:48,535
So I never had a family.

323
00:23:50,161 --> 00:23:52,831
I never thought about things
like marriage or kids.

324
00:23:54,332 --> 00:23:56,626
I've never even thought
about starting my own family.

325
00:23:58,211 --> 00:24:00,630
But when you just told me
you were pregnant...

326
00:24:01,381 --> 00:24:02,382
I mean...

327
00:24:03,174 --> 00:24:05,260
I don't know what this feeling is.

328
00:24:06,845 --> 00:24:07,929
But it made me think...

329
00:24:10,515 --> 00:24:13,101
That no matter what happens

330
00:24:14,561 --> 00:24:16,145
I want to be with you and our child.

331
00:24:19,232 --> 00:24:21,609
Let's get married, O-ran.

332
00:24:45,925 --> 00:24:47,968
Ho-myeong, why are you out here?

333
00:24:47,969 --> 00:24:50,929
- Why aren't you coming in?
- Oh, you scared me.

334
00:24:50,930 --> 00:24:53,057
Didn't you come here
to make up with O-ran?

335
00:24:58,938 --> 00:25:00,773
You brought the letter, right?

336
00:25:01,858 --> 00:25:04,026
- No.
- What? Why not?

337
00:25:04,027 --> 00:25:05,153
Well, I just...

338
00:25:06,154 --> 00:25:10,699
- I didn't know what to write.
- You still don't get O-ran?

339
00:25:10,700 --> 00:25:14,995
She'll forgive you
if you just say the right things.

340
00:25:14,996 --> 00:25:17,165
She's that easygoing, just like me.

341
00:25:18,791 --> 00:25:22,378
Well, this time,
I don't know if a few words will do.

342
00:25:23,755 --> 00:25:25,465
And I'm the one at fault.

343
00:25:25,590 --> 00:25:28,343
I think I'll just make her angrier.

344
00:25:33,222 --> 00:25:36,768
Do you know
why I came to Yeongseon Island?

345
00:25:38,436 --> 00:25:39,728
You said it was your hometown.

346
00:25:39,729 --> 00:25:41,229
It's not.

347
00:25:41,230 --> 00:25:43,440
I was going to open a store in Seoul.

348
00:25:43,441 --> 00:25:46,069
But I lost the money in a scam,
so I had no choice.

349
00:25:46,611 --> 00:25:47,612
What?

350
00:25:48,613 --> 00:25:52,408
I couldn't tell my wife.
My pride wouldn't let me.

351
00:25:53,076 --> 00:25:55,160
So I just lied to her.

352
00:25:55,161 --> 00:25:58,331
I told her wanted to settle down
in my hometown.

353
00:26:00,208 --> 00:26:03,877
My wife must have suspected something.

354
00:26:03,878 --> 00:26:05,587
But she didn't say a word.

355
00:26:05,588 --> 00:26:08,383
Even though she was pregnant,
she followed me without a complaint.

356
00:26:09,467 --> 00:26:12,302
I figured if she knew I'd been scammed,
she'd only be heartbroken.

357
00:26:12,303 --> 00:26:13,845
So I kept it from her.

358
00:26:13,846 --> 00:26:18,308
I thought I'd tell her
once the restaurant had found its place.

359
00:26:18,309 --> 00:26:19,602
But then...

360
00:26:20,728 --> 00:26:22,355
I never got to tell her.

361
00:26:26,693 --> 00:26:29,237
I should have just told her.

362
00:26:30,363 --> 00:26:32,656
Why did she work so hard every day?

363
00:26:32,657 --> 00:26:33,950
She wasn't well.

364
00:26:35,076 --> 00:26:37,537
She never even made time
to go to a hospital.

365
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:43,126
I wish I'd told her.

366
00:26:44,127 --> 00:26:46,796
Maybe she would've hated me
a little less when she passed.

367
00:26:52,051 --> 00:26:54,261
Don't leave any stupid regrets like I did.

368
00:26:54,262 --> 00:26:56,096
Be open with each other.

369
00:26:56,097 --> 00:26:59,142
That's what marriage is all about, right?

370
00:26:59,892 --> 00:27:01,144
Don't let O-ran...

371
00:27:02,061 --> 00:27:03,896
Don't let my daughter
be upset for so long.

372
00:27:07,191 --> 00:27:11,111
- Yes, I understand.
- Yeah? Let's go right now.

373
00:27:11,112 --> 00:27:13,740
Right now, I have something
I need to sort out.

374
00:27:14,574 --> 00:27:17,951
Next time I'm around, I'll tell her.

375
00:27:17,952 --> 00:27:23,791
I'll tell O-ran everything
that I haven't been able to.

376
00:27:25,585 --> 00:27:26,836
Geez.

377
00:27:28,546 --> 00:27:29,630
You know, right?

378
00:27:30,339 --> 00:27:31,841
An apology is all about timing.

379
00:27:33,301 --> 00:27:35,887
Yes. I won't be too late.

380
00:27:47,774 --> 00:27:51,818
It's been forever
since I've had the spotlight.

381
00:27:51,819 --> 00:27:53,029
I'm getting nervous.

382
00:27:54,864 --> 00:27:56,824
Give me one last update, will you?

383
00:27:57,575 --> 00:27:59,535
You've cut off
all funding for the orphanage, right?

384
00:28:00,953 --> 00:28:02,914
Oh, you shouldn't have.

385
00:28:10,421 --> 00:28:14,050
Thanks to Deputy Director Han,
it all went smoothly.

386
00:28:14,634 --> 00:28:15,717
Sir!

387
00:28:15,718 --> 00:28:19,012
We could say they didn't qualify
due to their outdated facilities.

388
00:28:19,013 --> 00:28:21,932
It's not even
the scheduled inspection date.

389
00:28:21,933 --> 00:28:24,559
It's a surprise inspection, ma'am.

390
00:28:24,560 --> 00:28:26,854
If we gave you a notice,
how would it be a surprise?

391
00:28:28,314 --> 00:28:30,398
Their financial situation is obvious.

392
00:28:30,399 --> 00:28:32,442
It's true that
the facilities are outdated.

393
00:28:32,443 --> 00:28:36,738
But still, if you do this so suddenly,
where are our children supposed to go?

394
00:28:36,739 --> 00:28:39,950
In any case, we have issued a warning
as per protocol.

395
00:28:39,951 --> 00:28:42,285
You can either use your own money
to make the repairs

396
00:28:42,286 --> 00:28:43,662
or shut the place down.

397
00:28:43,663 --> 00:28:45,163
Whatever you need to do.

398
00:28:45,164 --> 00:28:49,876
With no money to fix up the place,
they'll end up doing as we intended.

399
00:28:49,877 --> 00:28:52,838
- What about donors?
- They didn't have any major ones.

400
00:28:52,839 --> 00:28:56,633
Besides government subsidies,
it's all small donations from individuals.

401
00:28:56,634 --> 00:29:00,221
And most of that is Kim Seon-jung
and his wife's personal funds.

402
00:29:00,930 --> 00:29:03,933
That's why it's a problem
when you're too squeaky clean.

403
00:29:04,767 --> 00:29:06,434
Okay, good job.

404
00:29:06,435 --> 00:29:07,979
Now then.

405
00:29:08,729 --> 00:29:12,441
Shall I go and help myself
to the feast that's been laid out?

406
00:29:16,904 --> 00:29:18,738
Hello, sir.

407
00:29:18,739 --> 00:29:21,658
- How have you been?
- Good. How about you?

408
00:29:21,659 --> 00:29:22,784
That's good.

409
00:29:22,785 --> 00:29:24,327
Why can't we take out a loan?

410
00:29:24,328 --> 00:29:25,453
I'm sorry.

411
00:29:25,454 --> 00:29:27,706
But our decision is based on an evaluation

412
00:29:27,707 --> 00:29:29,749
of your credit rating
and collateral value.

413
00:29:29,750 --> 00:29:33,420
Your loan application
was denied in our internal review.

414
00:29:33,421 --> 00:29:36,047
But the manager said it was possible.

415
00:29:36,048 --> 00:29:38,634
Could you please check one more time?

416
00:29:42,972 --> 00:29:45,183
Excuse me, sir.

417
00:29:48,144 --> 00:29:51,229
- Oh, ma'am, what brings you here?
- Hello, sir.

418
00:29:51,230 --> 00:29:55,150
Ma'am, please, let's not do this here.
You can talk to me.

419
00:29:55,151 --> 00:29:56,401
Please.

420
00:29:56,402 --> 00:30:00,947
Why was the loan suddenly denied?
We're going to have to shut down.

421
00:30:00,948 --> 00:30:03,617
What are we supposed to do
with the children?

422
00:30:03,618 --> 00:30:05,119
Ah, excuse me.

423
00:30:05,953 --> 00:30:09,915
- What children?
- Oh, this lady runs an orphanage.

424
00:30:09,916 --> 00:30:12,001
And it seems there's been
a misunderstanding.

425
00:30:13,169 --> 00:30:17,131
Well, if you don't mind,
may I listen in on what she has to say?

426
00:30:17,590 --> 00:30:20,967
It's just that I don't quite understand
what's going on.

427
00:30:20,968 --> 00:30:25,723
This lady seems like a wonderful person
who dedicates herself to society.

428
00:30:26,307 --> 00:30:28,517
What's the reason
her loan was suddenly denied?

429
00:30:29,268 --> 00:30:31,187
Well, the thing is...

430
00:30:31,729 --> 00:30:35,524
When it comes to loans,
there are various policy-related factors.

431
00:30:36,400 --> 00:30:38,610
Exactly, those policies.

432
00:30:38,611 --> 00:30:42,197
They don't just change overnight, do they?
What do you think?

433
00:30:42,198 --> 00:30:45,408
Exactly.
You said it wasn't a problem last time.

434
00:30:45,409 --> 00:30:48,703
Sir, are you sure
you've reviewed this properly?

435
00:30:48,704 --> 00:30:49,913
Uh, well, that's...

436
00:30:49,914 --> 00:30:53,417
I've never seen a bank
change a loan policy overnight.

437
00:30:53,834 --> 00:30:55,795
I'm rapidly losing my faith
in this establishment.

438
00:30:56,504 --> 00:30:59,507
Who knows?
I could be in that lady's shoes.

439
00:31:00,174 --> 00:31:02,759
And you might
just flip on me just as easily.

440
00:31:02,760 --> 00:31:04,053
No, I would...

441
00:31:04,929 --> 00:31:06,514
That's... Ms. Kim.

442
00:31:07,098 --> 00:31:09,557
Bring me the documents
for the lady's loan.

443
00:31:09,558 --> 00:31:12,102
- I'll take a look myself.
- Yes, sir. Right away.

444
00:31:12,103 --> 00:31:13,145
Quickly.

445
00:31:15,773 --> 00:31:16,983
Excuse me.

446
00:31:18,651 --> 00:31:21,069
I never got a chance to thank you.

447
00:31:21,070 --> 00:31:22,654
Thank you so much.

448
00:31:22,655 --> 00:31:25,324
Oh, it was nothing.
Was everything resolved?

449
00:31:25,449 --> 00:31:26,908
Yes.

450
00:31:26,909 --> 00:31:28,953
Thanks to you,
I think the loan will be approved.

451
00:31:30,037 --> 00:31:33,708
- I can't thank you enough.
- Oh, never mind, never mind.

452
00:31:34,166 --> 00:31:37,878
You were so worried
the children would wind up on the streets.

453
00:31:39,297 --> 00:31:40,923
It reminded me of my past.

454
00:31:42,550 --> 00:31:45,177
When I was young,
my father's business failed.

455
00:31:45,303 --> 00:31:47,220
And I was homeless in the Philippines.

456
00:31:47,221 --> 00:31:49,055
Oh, no. Really?

457
00:31:49,056 --> 00:31:52,268
I made a promise to myself back then.

458
00:31:53,311 --> 00:31:56,981
That I would never turn my back
on someone in need.

459
00:31:57,273 --> 00:32:00,358
But I'd forgotten all about it
just because I got a little busy.

460
00:32:00,359 --> 00:32:04,488
You clearly haven't.
You helped our children so much today.

461
00:32:04,613 --> 00:32:06,532
Not at all. On the contrary.

462
00:32:07,366 --> 00:32:11,494
Meeting you today has made me
reflect on a lot of things.

463
00:32:11,495 --> 00:32:14,039
I've been so focused on getting ahead

464
00:32:14,040 --> 00:32:17,584
that I haven't looked
at the world around me.

465
00:32:17,585 --> 00:32:19,378
And frankly, I'm ashamed of myself.

466
00:32:21,672 --> 00:32:23,214
Which brings me to my point.

467
00:32:23,215 --> 00:32:25,300
You don't have to say yes.

468
00:32:25,301 --> 00:32:29,346
But would it be okay
if I sent a small gift to the children?

469
00:32:29,347 --> 00:32:32,016
- What?
- Ah, a gift. Yes?

470
00:32:33,142 --> 00:32:35,643
As long as you follow
the proper procedure.

471
00:32:35,644 --> 00:32:39,482
Oh, it's not that big of a gift
that'd require formal procedures.

472
00:32:40,066 --> 00:32:42,777
As long as you say yes, that is.

473
00:32:44,779 --> 00:32:47,823
We try to run our organization
as transparently as possible.

474
00:32:47,948 --> 00:32:52,118
We don't accept any private donations
of cash or goods.

475
00:32:52,119 --> 00:32:54,913
I'm sorry, but we'll only have to
accept your kind words.

476
00:32:54,914 --> 00:32:56,247
No.

477
00:32:56,248 --> 00:33:00,336
It's really not a big deal at all,
so I'm actually a bit embarrassed.

478
00:33:01,629 --> 00:33:05,340
Have we disposed of all the old books
from our hotel lounge?

479
00:33:05,341 --> 00:33:07,468
- Not yet.
- All right.

480
00:33:08,177 --> 00:33:11,513
It may not be much,
but what if I gave them these books?

481
00:33:11,514 --> 00:33:13,933
The idea just popped into my head.

482
00:33:14,058 --> 00:33:17,560
- Oh, the books?
- Yes. The books.

483
00:33:17,561 --> 00:33:20,898
It's not money or material things.
Just food for thought?

484
00:33:22,024 --> 00:33:26,362
It's just a few old books.
Would that be a problem too?

485
00:33:29,949 --> 00:33:32,076
WE OPPOSE YEONGSEON REDEVELOPMENT

486
00:33:57,643 --> 00:34:00,855
It was brief,
but the way he moved was not ordinary.

487
00:34:04,650 --> 00:34:06,318
And he has amnesia?

488
00:34:07,194 --> 00:34:09,780
There's so much
that's suspicious about him.

489
00:34:15,619 --> 00:34:20,206
Look. Prosecutor Gang has been
staring at Je-sun like that for a while.

490
00:34:20,206 --> 00:34:23,710
Something's definitely
going on between them.

491
00:34:24,628 --> 00:34:27,630
No way.
She just looks like she wants a fight.

492
00:34:27,630 --> 00:34:28,841
What would you know?

493
00:34:29,341 --> 00:34:30,384
You've never had a man.

494
00:34:38,893 --> 00:34:41,728
Mr. Bong.
Something happened between you two, right?

495
00:34:44,273 --> 00:34:46,024
Nothing happened.

496
00:34:46,025 --> 00:34:48,610
I was quite the heartbreaker
back in my day.

497
00:34:49,277 --> 00:34:51,614
When a woman gives you a look like that?

498
00:34:51,739 --> 00:34:55,074
It's either you owe her money,
or she's into you.

499
00:34:58,704 --> 00:35:00,414
It's so delicious.

500
00:35:03,501 --> 00:35:04,751
Be honest.

501
00:35:04,752 --> 00:35:06,669
You're into her too, aren't you?

502
00:35:06,670 --> 00:35:09,882
Come on, it's not like that. It's just...

503
00:35:10,966 --> 00:35:13,302
I mean, we've gotten kind of close.

504
00:35:13,844 --> 00:35:17,848
I'm just gonna bring the Sergeant
some soup in.

505
00:35:25,064 --> 00:35:26,649
Busy, busy.

506
00:35:28,234 --> 00:35:29,568
This was so delicious.

507
00:35:30,569 --> 00:35:31,946
I'll do the dishes tomorrow.

508
00:35:44,542 --> 00:35:46,043
Eat up.

509
00:35:49,547 --> 00:35:52,298
Hey, mister. Could you untie me, please?

510
00:35:52,299 --> 00:35:54,551
I'm not a criminal. What is this?

511
00:35:54,552 --> 00:35:55,928
Eat up.

512
00:35:58,514 --> 00:36:00,641
Come on, how can I eat
with my hands tied like this?

513
00:36:07,523 --> 00:36:08,899
Eat up.

514
00:36:11,735 --> 00:36:13,570
Damn it.

515
00:36:13,571 --> 00:36:15,572
This is a felony, you know that?

516
00:36:15,573 --> 00:36:20,244
The real felony is what you
and the Heaven Capital guys committed.

517
00:36:20,828 --> 00:36:23,914
Fine, don't eat if you don't want to.
What a waste of rice. Jeez.

518
00:36:24,623 --> 00:36:25,958
Wait, wait.

519
00:36:26,709 --> 00:36:30,170
Wait, are you the martial arts master
Heaven Capital was looking for?

520
00:36:30,296 --> 00:36:32,088
You fought them 17 to 1? Or was it 18?

521
00:36:32,089 --> 00:36:34,090
And the way you moved yesterday...

522
00:36:34,091 --> 00:36:35,466
It is you!

523
00:36:35,467 --> 00:36:36,676
Listen, sir.

524
00:36:36,677 --> 00:36:38,052
It's a pleasure to meet you.

525
00:36:38,053 --> 00:36:39,304
Please untie me.

526
00:36:39,305 --> 00:36:41,806
If you let me go,
I'll have a word with those guys.

527
00:36:41,807 --> 00:36:44,684
I'll tell them to stop chasing you.

528
00:36:44,685 --> 00:36:45,728
I promise. Okay?

529
00:36:50,065 --> 00:36:51,692
Just, uh... Eat your food.

530
00:37:11,253 --> 00:37:12,755
What the...

531
00:37:13,839 --> 00:37:15,049
What are you doing?

532
00:37:17,509 --> 00:37:20,262
Oh, I felt so dizzy
that I had to lean against the door.

533
00:37:25,267 --> 00:37:26,268
Goodness.

534
00:37:38,572 --> 00:37:39,573
Go ahead and eat.

535
00:37:45,412 --> 00:37:50,084
Here we go.

536
00:37:55,506 --> 00:37:56,757
You look cheerful.

537
00:37:57,216 --> 00:37:59,510
Feeling better
now that the loan came through?

538
00:38:00,511 --> 00:38:03,180
Of course. I was worried sick.

539
00:38:03,514 --> 00:38:08,102
Guess what? Someone I met at the bank
wants to make a donation.

540
00:38:09,395 --> 00:38:11,229
A donation? Who?

541
00:38:11,230 --> 00:38:15,275
Chairman Do Hyeon-tae of the Heaven Hotel.
He said they have used books.

542
00:38:15,401 --> 00:38:17,820
He'd rather donate them to the kids
than throw them away.

543
00:38:20,072 --> 00:38:21,115
Do Hyeon-tae...

544
00:38:22,449 --> 00:38:23,784
The Chairman of Heaven Casino?

545
00:38:25,661 --> 00:38:28,664
He's never shown any interest
in public service.

546
00:38:29,081 --> 00:38:30,874
Why suddenly make a donation?

547
00:38:33,544 --> 00:38:34,712
That's odd.

548
00:38:37,631 --> 00:38:40,050
Honey, you have to turn it down.

549
00:38:41,552 --> 00:38:42,553
What?

550
00:38:43,303 --> 00:38:46,180
It's a book donation, not money.

551
00:38:46,181 --> 00:38:50,393
Still, who knows
what the man is really after?

552
00:38:50,394 --> 00:38:53,187
Anyway, don't take anything from him,
books or otherwise.

553
00:38:53,188 --> 00:38:55,481
You've really turned into a politician,
haven't you?

554
00:38:55,482 --> 00:38:57,608
It was a kind offer.

555
00:38:57,609 --> 00:38:59,736
And you can't see it
as anything but suspicious?

556
00:38:59,737 --> 00:39:02,155
That's not it.
I'm just saying we should be careful.

557
00:39:02,156 --> 00:39:05,366
It's just a few used books.
What is there to be so careful about?

558
00:39:05,367 --> 00:39:08,245
Should the children go without books
because of your political ambitions?

559
00:39:17,212 --> 00:39:20,047
You're right. I overreacted.

560
00:39:20,048 --> 00:39:23,135
It's just a few used books.
Take them. All right?

561
00:39:23,719 --> 00:39:25,721
- Really?
- Yeah.

562
00:39:34,229 --> 00:39:38,608
Chairman, we've received the used books.

563
00:39:38,609 --> 00:39:40,903
Thank you for your generous donation.

564
00:39:42,029 --> 00:39:43,738
Your kindness

565
00:39:43,739 --> 00:39:47,117
will be food for the soul
for everyone here.

566
00:39:52,080 --> 00:39:54,041
The package is delivered.

567
00:39:56,585 --> 00:39:59,630
I made a special selection
from my most prized collections.

568
00:40:00,881 --> 00:40:03,091
You didn't just drop them off
and leave, did you?

569
00:40:04,218 --> 00:40:05,802
Of course not.

570
00:40:05,803 --> 00:40:08,764
I've already spoken to an employee.

571
00:40:10,307 --> 00:40:12,767
I told him he'd be ruined
by gambling debts

572
00:40:12,768 --> 00:40:15,437
if he didn't get rid of
those paintings for us.

573
00:40:16,271 --> 00:40:19,315
It's to be sold off without her knowing,
and the money will be discreetly deposited

574
00:40:19,316 --> 00:40:22,360
into the organization's bank account
as a donation.

575
00:40:22,361 --> 00:40:24,821
Just push the button

576
00:40:24,822 --> 00:40:27,740
and Kim Seon-jung will no longer be

577
00:40:27,741 --> 00:40:29,867
the honest mayoral candidate
everyone loves.

578
00:40:29,868 --> 00:40:33,288
He'll be a man who used a charity
to raise illegal political funds.

579
00:40:33,747 --> 00:40:36,208
A corrupt politician
who's no better than trash.

580
00:40:39,670 --> 00:40:41,713
- Well done.
- Thank you.

581
00:40:42,297 --> 00:40:43,340
So...

582
00:40:43,841 --> 00:40:44,967
Shall I set off the package?

583
00:40:45,092 --> 00:40:46,468
If we're going to set it off

584
00:40:47,427 --> 00:40:49,346
it might as well be a good show.

585
00:40:49,888 --> 00:40:51,765
- What do you mean?
- Baek.

586
00:40:52,140 --> 00:40:53,141
Yes.

587
00:40:53,642 --> 00:40:56,812
Let's go grab some soup soon.

588
00:40:56,937 --> 00:40:58,105
Understood.

589
00:41:04,444 --> 00:41:06,028
Hey, what are you talking about?

590
00:41:06,029 --> 00:41:07,406
I was planning on going.

591
00:41:07,906 --> 00:41:10,576
But we've been after this broker
for the last three months.

592
00:41:10,868 --> 00:41:13,078
Hey, this is a huge case.

593
00:41:14,580 --> 00:41:15,998
Okay, just listen.

594
00:41:16,748 --> 00:41:19,041
If you can't make it,
at least send someone else.

595
00:41:19,042 --> 00:41:21,044
This broker is a big deal too.

596
00:41:21,336 --> 00:41:23,129
Plus, it's the chief's orders.

597
00:41:23,130 --> 00:41:24,755
Everyone here is on it.

598
00:41:24,756 --> 00:41:26,048
I'll be right behind you.

599
00:41:26,049 --> 00:41:27,133
Anyway...

600
00:41:27,134 --> 00:41:29,010
Please just gather some evidence for now.

601
00:41:29,011 --> 00:41:30,636
I'll be there as soon as I'm done.

602
00:41:30,637 --> 00:41:33,681
Screw the evidence.
You should be raiding the place!

603
00:41:33,682 --> 00:41:34,683
Hello?

604
00:41:39,855 --> 00:41:43,191
I thought they were just stealing money,
but they're bringing in drugs too.

605
00:41:44,234 --> 00:41:47,361
- You're the worst kind of scum.
- Look.

606
00:41:47,362 --> 00:41:50,364
These corrupt cops
and the Heaven Capital guys...

607
00:41:50,365 --> 00:41:54,870
If Prosecutor Gang links them to drugs,
can we really round them all up?

608
00:41:55,454 --> 00:41:57,455
We should be able to, right?

609
00:41:57,456 --> 00:41:59,582
It'll clean up the precinct, for sure.

610
00:41:59,583 --> 00:42:04,295
If they all go to prison,
everything they did will be revealed.

611
00:42:04,296 --> 00:42:06,548
If things go well,
I might get my house back.

612
00:42:07,633 --> 00:42:08,634
Hey, I'm sorry.

613
00:42:09,551 --> 00:42:12,470
I don't think the raid we planned
with the detectives today

614
00:42:12,471 --> 00:42:13,554
is going to happen.

615
00:42:13,555 --> 00:42:15,765
- Why not?
- What?

616
00:42:15,766 --> 00:42:18,267
So, are we supposed to
just sit here and watch?

617
00:42:18,268 --> 00:42:20,145
Oh, no. I'll go alone if I have to.

618
00:42:20,395 --> 00:42:22,981
I have to secure evidence
for there to be a next step.

619
00:42:23,273 --> 00:42:25,567
- All by yourself?
- Want to come with me then?

620
00:42:26,360 --> 00:42:28,903
Mi-kyung, would you mind coming with me?

621
00:42:28,904 --> 00:42:30,155
- Okay.
- Wait!

622
00:42:30,781 --> 00:42:32,658
I have to go too. I'm no civilian.

623
00:42:32,908 --> 00:42:35,284
- I'll be useful.
- I'm coming, too.

624
00:42:35,285 --> 00:42:37,703
I have to catch them to get my house back.

625
00:42:37,704 --> 00:42:39,705
I'll do anything. Please let me.

626
00:42:39,706 --> 00:42:43,710
Hold on.
That place is extremely dangerous.

627
00:42:44,252 --> 00:42:46,504
Then that's all the more reason
for us to go.

628
00:42:46,505 --> 00:42:48,632
We can't send you off all alone.

629
00:42:50,509 --> 00:42:51,510
- Right?
- Yes.

630
00:42:57,099 --> 00:42:58,642
- Welcome back, Boss!
- Welcome back, Boss!

631
00:42:59,267 --> 00:43:00,476
Is this everyone?

632
00:43:00,477 --> 00:43:01,478
Yes, Boss.

633
00:43:03,522 --> 00:43:07,359
As I told you before,
we must move without Han and Do noticing.

634
00:43:08,151 --> 00:43:09,152
This is the best we can do.

635
00:43:09,569 --> 00:43:12,406
Han and Do.
Those two are always getting in the way.

636
00:43:13,115 --> 00:43:14,407
Don't worry, sir.

637
00:43:14,408 --> 00:43:17,244
I have about thirty kids
on standby at the port.

638
00:43:17,661 --> 00:43:21,415
Martial arts master or not,
he can't handle that many people alone.

639
00:43:22,082 --> 00:43:23,917
Gotta make do with what we've got.

640
00:43:24,668 --> 00:43:27,170
Today is a historic day for the Ingu Sect.

641
00:43:28,005 --> 00:43:30,048
Anyone who screws up will die at my hand.

642
00:43:31,216 --> 00:43:34,011
- So you'd better stay sharp!
- Yes, Boss!

643
00:43:41,018 --> 00:43:43,020
- Hey, you're here.
- Hey, Jin-su.

644
00:43:43,145 --> 00:43:45,439
- Nam-il's here too.
- Heard the pay was good.

645
00:43:49,651 --> 00:43:53,363
- Why did you bring Nam-il?
- He said he was desperate for cash.

646
00:43:54,031 --> 00:43:55,032
Just cut him some slack.

647
00:43:55,991 --> 00:43:58,577
Hey, but what are we even doing here?

648
00:44:00,120 --> 00:44:02,080
- Why do we need these tools?
- Beats me.

649
00:44:37,741 --> 00:44:38,867
Evening, Boss!

650
00:44:39,576 --> 00:44:41,160
This kid's got some fight in him.

651
00:44:41,161 --> 00:44:43,205
- Get your head up.
- Yes, Boss!

652
00:44:43,663 --> 00:44:45,915
- Is everyone here?
- Yes! They're all here.

653
00:44:45,916 --> 00:44:47,542
- Okay. To your posts.
- To your posts!

654
00:44:52,089 --> 00:44:53,422
Listen up.

655
00:44:53,423 --> 00:44:57,135
A very important package
is arriving today for the Ingu Sect.

656
00:44:57,260 --> 00:45:01,764
Your job is to secure said package.

657
00:45:01,765 --> 00:45:03,600
And to make sure no one steals it.

658
00:45:04,893 --> 00:45:06,353
Those of you who do well today

659
00:45:07,187 --> 00:45:10,815
will be made full-time members
of the Ingu Sect with full benefits.

660
00:45:10,816 --> 00:45:12,776
- Got it?
- Yes, sir!

661
00:45:15,654 --> 00:45:17,154
What's this kid's problem?

662
00:45:17,155 --> 00:45:18,323
Hey, move over.

663
00:45:20,367 --> 00:45:21,368
What?

664
00:45:22,577 --> 00:45:23,620
Huh?

665
00:45:24,579 --> 00:45:25,622
Hey, you punk. Get over here.

666
00:45:26,498 --> 00:45:29,125
- Why?
- Get over here. Hey, grab him.

667
00:45:29,126 --> 00:45:30,585
Hey, get him!

668
00:45:34,548 --> 00:45:35,924
Get over here.

669
00:45:37,717 --> 00:45:38,718
Boss.

670
00:45:41,388 --> 00:45:43,222
Aren't you
the martial arts master's nephew?

671
00:45:43,223 --> 00:45:44,557
Huh?

672
00:45:44,558 --> 00:45:46,059
- No, I'm not.
- It is, Boss.

673
00:45:46,309 --> 00:45:48,728
- You've got the wrong guy.
- I know it's you.

674
00:45:49,437 --> 00:45:51,522
What did I tell you? I was right.

675
00:45:51,523 --> 00:45:53,525
The martial arts master is here.

676
00:45:54,526 --> 00:45:58,196
He even planted his nephew as a mole.
He really came prepared.

677
00:45:58,780 --> 00:46:00,907
- What should we do, Boss?
- What else?

678
00:46:01,950 --> 00:46:03,826
The winning hand just fell into our hands.

679
00:46:03,827 --> 00:46:05,245
We just gratefully accept it.

680
00:46:07,455 --> 00:46:10,167
You're a little adorable rat, aren't you?

681
00:46:30,645 --> 00:46:34,065
Man, it feels great to be
out in the field again.

682
00:46:35,317 --> 00:46:36,526
So what do we do now?

683
00:46:37,277 --> 00:46:39,905
Do we mess up
those Heaven Capital guys now?

684
00:46:40,989 --> 00:46:42,364
Sorry, guys.

685
00:46:42,365 --> 00:46:44,533
I think I'd better go alone from here.

686
00:46:44,534 --> 00:46:46,577
But what are you going to do on your own?

687
00:46:46,578 --> 00:46:49,288
What? Why?
I was hoping to finally get some action.

688
00:46:49,289 --> 00:46:53,500
If we move as a group out here,
we'll be way too noticeable.

689
00:46:53,501 --> 00:46:55,753
I'll go in alone and secure the evidence.

690
00:46:55,754 --> 00:46:58,924
- You can wait in the car.
- Wait, just a moment.

691
00:47:00,759 --> 00:47:01,760
Come on.

692
00:47:04,596 --> 00:47:05,639
Listen.

693
00:47:06,723 --> 00:47:07,891
In case anything happens

694
00:47:09,017 --> 00:47:10,267
use this radio.

695
00:47:10,268 --> 00:47:11,352
I'll come running.

696
00:47:11,353 --> 00:47:13,230
Thank you. I'll be right back.

697
00:47:18,985 --> 00:47:21,363
- We would be noticeable.
- Very.

698
00:47:28,912 --> 00:47:31,288
But I really think I should follow her.

699
00:47:31,289 --> 00:47:34,334
- She said not to.
- She's in no condition for this.

700
00:47:35,085 --> 00:47:38,129
She's still not fully recovered.
Someone should be with her. I'll go.

701
00:47:40,215 --> 00:47:41,508
Okay.

702
00:47:41,716 --> 00:47:43,884
- I'll be right back. Just wait here.
- Wait.

703
00:47:43,885 --> 00:47:44,970
Prosecutor Gang!

704
00:47:45,512 --> 00:47:46,638
See that?

705
00:47:46,888 --> 00:47:48,556
There's something going on between them.

706
00:47:59,651 --> 00:48:00,652
Are you okay?

707
00:48:01,486 --> 00:48:02,487
Yeah.

708
00:48:11,621 --> 00:48:14,416
- Is it all in there?
- Have I ever let you down?

709
00:48:15,333 --> 00:48:16,334
You can see for yourself.

710
00:48:36,146 --> 00:48:38,857
By the way,
why'd you call in so many people?

711
00:48:39,566 --> 00:48:42,818
- Is there some kind of problem?
- What problem?

712
00:48:42,819 --> 00:48:44,486
Let's say they're moral support.

713
00:48:44,487 --> 00:48:48,073
Well then, the goods are checked.

714
00:48:48,074 --> 00:48:49,784
And you've got your moral support.

715
00:48:50,076 --> 00:48:52,120
Please sign the delivery receipt.

716
00:48:58,293 --> 00:48:59,376
Good work.

717
00:48:59,377 --> 00:49:01,795
We got paid and the delivery went well.
It's a win-win.

718
00:49:01,796 --> 00:49:04,382
I'll let the guys in mainland know
that the deal went smoothly.

719
00:49:06,676 --> 00:49:08,470
I've been waiting for this day.

720
00:49:09,471 --> 00:49:10,805
Ah, what a beauty.

721
00:49:11,681 --> 00:49:13,724
Hey, let's grab it and get out of here.

722
00:49:13,725 --> 00:49:16,186
- Let's not waste time. Got it?
- Yes, sir.

723
00:49:18,772 --> 00:49:20,273
Hey, Kim. Bring it down.

724
00:49:21,441 --> 00:49:22,650
Yes, sir.

725
00:49:33,286 --> 00:49:36,081
We're all set here.
It's time to have some fun.

726
00:49:41,419 --> 00:49:42,420
What the hell?

727
00:49:44,130 --> 00:49:45,131
Go check that out.

728
00:49:46,257 --> 00:49:47,425
Kim, I said pull it down.

729
00:49:50,512 --> 00:49:52,222
Didn't you hear me? Get it down!

730
00:49:55,433 --> 00:49:56,476
Mr. Yoo?

731
00:49:58,019 --> 00:49:59,896
What's going on here?

732
00:50:03,191 --> 00:50:05,860
This is well within my expectations.
No need to panic.

733
00:50:08,279 --> 00:50:10,198
What are you waiting for?
Did you forget Plan B?

734
00:50:13,618 --> 00:50:16,412
All right, kids, get ready for Plan B.

735
00:50:16,413 --> 00:50:17,414
Let's go!

736
00:50:18,331 --> 00:50:19,624
- Focus. Get ready.
- Yeah.

737
00:50:24,504 --> 00:50:25,672
Damn it, what is that?

738
00:50:28,675 --> 00:50:29,883
Come on, kids.

739
00:50:29,884 --> 00:50:33,179
You should be holding pencils,
not weapons.

740
00:50:35,682 --> 00:50:37,475
Focus!

741
00:50:38,935 --> 00:50:40,270
- Go!
- Let's go!

742
00:50:42,814 --> 00:50:44,691
What the hell?

743
00:50:45,775 --> 00:50:47,360
Hey, are we supposed to jump?

744
00:50:49,863 --> 00:50:51,864
- Everyone get ready.
- Yes, sir.

745
00:50:51,865 --> 00:50:54,075
Boys!

746
00:50:59,956 --> 00:51:01,040
Look, Boss!

747
00:51:05,295 --> 00:51:07,045
Martial Arts Master.

748
00:51:07,046 --> 00:51:09,256
I was wondering when you'd show up.

749
00:51:09,257 --> 00:51:11,509
- Two of you this time.
- How many times do I have to say it?

750
00:51:12,260 --> 00:51:16,556
I said it's Masked Racer. Masked Racer!

751
00:51:17,974 --> 00:51:19,684
That masked freak is back.

752
00:51:20,435 --> 00:51:22,561
Whatever you are,
why do you keep showing up

753
00:51:22,562 --> 00:51:24,271
and messing with my business?

754
00:51:24,272 --> 00:51:28,818
Masked Racer keeps appearing
because you keep doing bad things.

755
00:51:29,652 --> 00:51:30,653
But today?

756
00:51:31,070 --> 00:51:34,491
I didn't come to mess with you.
I came to see the first snow.

757
00:51:36,367 --> 00:51:37,952
What is he on about?

758
00:51:40,705 --> 00:51:45,335
You think I'd just nod my head
and let you get away?

759
00:51:46,544 --> 00:51:49,756
I knew you'd be here,
so I already dug your grave, you bastard.

760
00:51:50,590 --> 00:51:53,300
You can't just rely on numbers
to win a fight.

761
00:51:53,301 --> 00:51:55,178
You have to use your head.

762
00:51:56,387 --> 00:51:59,724
Well, we've finally gathered
all of you good people in one place.

763
00:52:00,642 --> 00:52:02,060
So what do you say?

764
00:52:02,644 --> 00:52:04,521
Shall we watch the first snow together?

765
00:52:31,839 --> 00:52:32,966
What's wrong with this thing?

766
00:52:34,175 --> 00:52:35,718
Hey, you gotta press it harder.

767
00:52:40,682 --> 00:52:41,683
That's not it.

768
00:52:44,978 --> 00:52:46,478
Dude, it's not working.

769
00:52:46,479 --> 00:52:48,188
Crap, could it have gotten too old?

770
00:52:48,189 --> 00:52:50,984
Hey, Ho-myeong, press it harder.
Really push it.

771
00:52:52,527 --> 00:52:55,154
Just press it harder, you idiot!

772
00:52:57,448 --> 00:52:58,950
Damn it, it's not working!

773
00:52:59,450 --> 00:53:00,659
Is this thing broken?

774
00:53:00,660 --> 00:53:02,203
- What the hell?
- Damn it.

775
00:53:05,456 --> 00:53:07,709
- Press it harder.
- What the hell are they doing?

776
00:53:08,710 --> 00:53:10,628
Find out how that bastard
climbed up there.

777
00:53:11,921 --> 00:53:13,047
Oh, come on!

778
00:53:15,425 --> 00:53:16,426
Damn it!

779
00:53:58,843 --> 00:53:59,844
Damn it!

780
00:54:03,306 --> 00:54:04,556
- No!
- No.

781
00:54:04,557 --> 00:54:06,142
Get all those guys!

782
00:56:36,375 --> 00:56:37,960
I'll kill those bastards!

783
00:56:39,045 --> 00:56:40,880
Hey, bring me the nephew.

784
00:56:51,891 --> 00:56:55,019
- What are you doing here?
- Wasn't there a gunshot just now?

785
00:56:55,353 --> 00:56:57,396
You have no idea
how dangerous those guys are.

786
00:56:58,523 --> 00:57:00,274
- Stay perfectly still.
- Okay.

787
00:57:05,488 --> 00:57:07,865
- Did you get enough evidence?
- I am right now.

788
00:57:08,699 --> 00:57:10,409
This is a crucial moment.

789
00:57:14,539 --> 00:57:15,540
Stop!

790
00:57:16,749 --> 00:57:19,043
Stop unless you want to
watch this kid die!

791
00:57:19,585 --> 00:57:20,586
Nam-il.

792
00:57:20,878 --> 00:57:21,879
What did you say?

793
00:57:22,213 --> 00:57:23,464
My nephew, Nam-il.

794
00:57:24,048 --> 00:57:25,049
What's he doing there?

795
00:57:26,300 --> 00:57:28,010
What are you doing? Are you crazy?

796
00:57:28,135 --> 00:57:30,554
I have to save him.
He could die if he stays there.

797
00:57:30,555 --> 00:57:33,390
But what can you do? Do you have a plan?

798
00:57:33,391 --> 00:57:35,725
- Just wait. I'll radio it in.
- No.

799
00:57:35,726 --> 00:57:36,894
There's no time for that.

800
00:57:40,398 --> 00:57:42,525
Oh my god. What are you doing?

801
00:57:47,113 --> 00:57:50,323
Ms. Gang, please hit me in the head
with this as hard as you can.

802
00:57:50,324 --> 00:57:51,993
Are you insane?

803
00:57:55,162 --> 00:57:56,581
I have a plan.

804
00:57:57,248 --> 00:57:59,124
Just trust me.

805
00:57:59,125 --> 00:58:02,169
Hit me in the head as hard as you can.

806
00:58:02,295 --> 00:58:03,296
I'm begging you.

807
00:58:04,505 --> 00:58:05,589
Please.

808
00:58:05,590 --> 00:58:08,592
Hurry.

809
00:58:08,593 --> 00:58:10,720
Nam-il is going to die at this rate!

810
00:58:12,972 --> 00:58:13,973
Oh my god!

811
00:58:15,141 --> 00:58:16,183
Je-sun.

812
00:58:17,685 --> 00:58:19,228
This is crazy.

813
00:58:22,648 --> 00:58:25,067
Mi-kyung, bring the car here.
It's an emergency.

814
00:58:29,071 --> 00:58:30,155
Damn it.

815
00:58:30,156 --> 00:58:32,325
Go ahead if you want your nephew to die.

816
00:58:33,075 --> 00:58:34,618
Nephew? What nephew?

817
00:58:34,619 --> 00:58:35,661
Hey, you have a nephew?

818
00:58:35,786 --> 00:58:36,913
I don't have a nephew.

819
00:58:42,084 --> 00:58:43,794
Wait a minute. That kid.

820
00:58:44,754 --> 00:58:45,796
Isn't he Bulgae's nephew?

821
00:58:46,297 --> 00:58:47,714
Hey, don't do it!

822
00:58:47,715 --> 00:58:49,299
He's not one of us.

823
00:58:49,300 --> 00:58:52,553
You think I'll believe that?
I'm gonna slit his throat.

824
00:58:53,304 --> 00:58:55,306
- What the hell?
- Get those bastards!

825
00:59:26,837 --> 00:59:28,547
One...

826
00:59:29,966 --> 00:59:31,550
Two...

827
00:59:43,437 --> 00:59:44,939
Uncle!

828
01:00:13,884 --> 01:00:15,428
Screw you, scumbag gangsters!

829
01:00:17,430 --> 01:00:20,724
Come on! I dare you!
I'm Heo Nam-il! Got it?

830
01:00:20,725 --> 01:00:23,936
I'm not going down alone. I'll throw it!
I swear I'll throw it!

831
01:00:32,445 --> 01:00:34,821
- What happened?
- Step on it. Head that way.

832
01:00:34,822 --> 01:00:36,824
- Where's Bong?
- Over there.

833
01:00:52,381 --> 01:00:54,717
- Get in, quick!
- Hurry!

834
01:01:02,308 --> 01:01:03,309
We got it!

835
01:01:07,938 --> 01:01:08,939
Wake up!

836
01:01:09,690 --> 01:01:10,816
Is he hurt badly?

837
01:01:11,108 --> 01:01:12,902
I don't know.
I don't see any external injuries.

838
01:01:14,403 --> 01:01:17,197
- His breathing's normal too.
- He turned into the Hulk.

839
01:01:17,198 --> 01:01:18,282
The Hulk?

840
01:01:19,241 --> 01:01:20,785
He'll be fine in a little bit.

841
01:01:22,161 --> 01:01:23,703
My uncle's no ordinary person.

842
01:01:23,704 --> 01:01:26,415
Forget about that!
Why was he on the ground over there?

843
01:01:26,832 --> 01:01:28,208
Ah, Prosecutor Gang!

844
01:01:28,209 --> 01:01:30,461
You got the video you wanted, right?

845
01:01:30,795 --> 01:01:33,129
I did, but there were some complications.

846
01:01:33,130 --> 01:01:36,008
- Complications?
- Let's just get back. I'll tell you then.

847
01:01:48,729 --> 01:01:50,939
- Should we go?
- Yeah. You okay?

848
01:01:50,940 --> 01:01:51,941
Yeah.

849
01:01:53,442 --> 01:01:54,443
What is it?

850
01:01:56,028 --> 01:01:57,112
I recognize that car.

851
01:01:57,113 --> 01:01:59,865
- Whatever. Just go.
- Okay.

852
01:02:09,834 --> 01:02:11,919
- We're done here. Let's get out.
- Huh?

853
01:02:12,461 --> 01:02:13,629
- Hey, it's time.
- Let's go!

854
01:02:24,181 --> 01:02:26,225
Hey, Boss, wake up already!

855
01:02:28,561 --> 01:02:30,437
Go after them, you idiots!

856
01:02:32,231 --> 01:02:33,774
Those bastards! Damn it!

857
01:02:43,284 --> 01:02:44,952
Unbelievable.

858
01:02:46,579 --> 01:02:47,580
Let's go.

859
01:02:50,958 --> 01:02:53,668
- Go after them!
- What's wrong with this thing?

860
01:02:53,669 --> 01:02:55,920
- What now?
- Something's wrong with the car.

861
01:02:55,921 --> 01:02:57,923
- Why isn't it working?
- Damn it!

862
01:03:00,718 --> 01:03:02,094
YEONGSEON FOOD

863
01:03:08,809 --> 01:03:09,810
Hurry up, you idiot!

864
01:03:11,729 --> 01:03:12,730
Come on!

865
01:03:20,821 --> 01:03:22,531
Yeah!

866
01:03:27,703 --> 01:03:29,496
That was freaking rough!

867
01:03:41,592 --> 01:03:44,220
SPECIAL THANKS TO
KIM SANG-KYUNG AND KWON YUL

868
01:03:59,026 --> 01:04:02,363
So these so-called Masked Racers
suddenly appeared out of nowhere

869
01:04:02,488 --> 01:04:04,364
and blew up all the drugs?

870
01:04:04,365 --> 01:04:06,574
- Hey, Boss!
- A double agent?

871
01:04:06,575 --> 01:04:09,535
- You sure you can handle this?
- Patrolling is my specialty. Don't worry.

872
01:04:09,536 --> 01:04:11,997
Honestly, she seemed
very suspicious to me.

873
01:04:12,122 --> 01:04:14,332
So she approached
Gang Beom-ryong on purpose?

874
01:04:14,333 --> 01:04:15,750
I'll watch him closely.

875
01:04:15,751 --> 01:04:18,003
You think I'm stupid enough
to let something like this break me?

876
01:04:19,922 --> 01:04:21,547
Je-sun. I'm just asking.

877
01:04:21,548 --> 01:04:24,592
What would you do if your past self
was a completely different person?

878
01:04:24,593 --> 01:04:26,219
You turned into the Hulk yesterday.

879
01:04:26,220 --> 01:04:27,553
Jeong Ho-myeong and I

880
01:04:27,554 --> 01:04:29,180
could be back at each other's throats
at any moment.

881
01:04:29,181 --> 01:04:31,850
- You bastard.
- You're the only one I can count on.

882
01:04:31,976 --> 01:04:35,478
- It's not too late for you to pull out.
- Is this a threat?

883
01:04:35,479 --> 01:04:38,189
- Gather all of our boys.
- You have to take responsibility.

884
01:04:38,190 --> 01:04:40,693
- I'm already prepared.
- Where the hell did Bulgae come from?

885
01:04:40,818 --> 01:04:43,778
- It was Je-sun.
- This is no coincidence.

886
01:04:43,779 --> 01:04:45,239
Change of plans.
